gomodel:SYNGO_3118  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.3: \"Interaction of MAGUIN-1 with S-SCAM.\"\n- \"...interaction of S-SCAM with the C-terminal region of MAGUIN-1. The extract of COS cells expressing S-SCAM was incubated with either GST-MAGUIN-12 (the C-terminal construct of MAGUIN-1) ...\"\n\nFig.5: \"Interaction of MAGUIN-1 with PSD-95/SAP90\"\n- \"...coimmunoprecipitation of MAGUIN-1 with PSD-95/SAP90. The Triton X-100 extract of the rat crude synaptosomal fraction ...\"\n\nFig.7: \"Subcellular localization of MAGUINs\"\n- \"...In the subcellular fractionation of rat brain, MAGUINs were detected mainly in the synaptic plasma membrane (SPM) and PSD fractions (Fig.7 A)...\"\n- \"In rat hippocampal neurons, MAGUINs were distributed in the cell body and the neurites and colocalized with NMDAR1 (Fig. 7 B).\"\nNote: NMDARs are predominantly located in the PSD.\n\nFig.8: \"Membrane association of MAGUINs in CHO cells.\"\n- \"The PH domain is known to interact with the phospholipid membrane...these findings suggest that MAGUIN-1 associates with the plasma membrane through the region containing the PH domain and the C-terminal stretch of the PH domain...\"\n\nFig.10: \"Recruitment of PSD-95/SAP90 and S-SCAM into the Triton X-100-insoluble fraction by MAGUIN-1\"\n- \"A and B). MAGUIN-1 and -2 were distributed in the Triton X-100-insoluble fraction (Fig. 9 A and data not shown). PSD-95/SAP90 and S-SCAM were recruited into the Triton X-100-insoluble fraction, when coexpressed with MAGUIN-1 (Fig. 10, C and D). In contrast, PSD-95/SAP90 and S-SCAM remained in the Triton X-100-soluble fraction, when coexpressed with MAGUIN-2 (data not shown).\". Experimental description: - \"Other procedures, including subcellular fractionation of rat brain, primary cultures of rat hippocampal neurons,...\"\n- \"We obtained the presumptive full-length coding sequences of pPrey 4233 through the conventional hybridization screening using a rat brain cDNA library and polymerase chain reaction using rat brain cDNAs as templates. \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3118" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

